cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on self-supervised learning of spatio-temporal embeddings from video, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed Dense Predictive Coding (DPC) framework involves recurrently predicting future representations, which is a form of predictive modeling and could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the approach involves action recognition, which is a common task in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the curriculum training scheme involves progressively reducing the temporal context, which could be seen as a form of curriculum learning and could fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
